File: KZN police have launched an investigation. DURBAN - A man died during a shooting incident at Isipingo taxi rank on Monday. Another person is in critical condition. “We can confirm that this morning at 8:00 two men were allegedly approached by three men who fired shots at them. One was declared dead on the scene and the other was rushed to the hospital,” said KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson, Thulani Zwane. READ: One person injured after being shot at Bree Taxi Rank The two men were seated inside a taxi at Chester Meats on Inwabi Road in Isipingo Rail when the shooting occured. KZN police have opened a case of murder and have launched an investigation.